#ELLEDigitalCoverStars: In a world where ambition dominates, love often plays the quiet background score—until two people make it the melody that leads. But for Aashna Shroff (@aashnashroff) and Armaan Malik (@armaanmalik), their story is composed in perfect harmony—two forces navigating fame, fashion, and music, yet always finding their rhythm together. Naturally, our first question was about how a couple as dynamic as this came together. Shroff reminisces about the early days of their romance and says, “We started talking on and off in 2017 without any real expectations. Six months in, we found ourselves in New York at the same time, and that’s when we went on our first official date. It’s still one of my favourite memories.” Malik, always the storyteller, adds with a nostalgic smile, “A week later, jet-lagged in the middle of the night, I called her just to tell her how I felt. That moment changed everything.” Head to the 🔗 in bio to read the full conversation with our cover stars.

latestPosts.caption:
While we always knew our ceremony in December was what we would consider our actual wedding, this day actually ended up meaning so much more than we had imagined.

I wore my Nani’s wedding saree from 63 years ago, that I paired with my great grandmother’s jewellery (the green bangles were in honour of my Maharashtrian roots from their side), my mumma draped my saree, my best friend helped do my hair, I did my makeup with whatever I could find amidst the chaos, Armaan played my favourite song “Yeh Tune Kya Kiya” as I entered, and at 11:11 am on 22.04.2024, we got legally married in our first home together, then spent the afternoon with our family, laughing eating and soaking it all in, after which we both made ourselves cocktails and watched the sunset in our new balcony as husband and wife ❤️

Also there’s no way we could have made this day or our wedding happen if it weren’t for our home team @ateliereventsindia @thephotolabin 🤍 forever grateful for you guys @siddhesh_ghadi @prerna_joshi97 @harshforever @devanshrangani!
